ABUJA: Ahead of the general elections, the Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, on Wednesday assured the National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC) and former Lagos State governor, Bola Tinubu, of the support of the National Assembly in his presidential bid. The Senate President who was addressing the APC National Leader when the latter visited the APC Senate caucus, at the National Assembly, commended him for his efforts at ensuring the growth of democracy in the country; and for stabilizing the party. He disclosed the loyalty of APC Senators to the President Muhammadu Buhari led government, insisting that “APC Senate caucus is a Central, fundamental core of the Party.” Details to come.